name: The bird of the birth
description:
These people have learned not from books, but in the fields, in the wood, on the river bank. Their teachers have been the birds themselves, when they sang to them, the sun when it left a glow of crimson behind it at setting, the very trees, and wild herbs. - “Anton Chekhov Short Stories v2: Classic Russia Literature”.

An original artwork by Iskra Velitchkova. 5000x5000px JPG. Original PNG for collectors.
